Passive Income System (Updated Direction)

Passive income pays out 100% of current cube value per tick. No passive rate reduction.

Why the Reduction Was Removed

The original PassiveRate = 0.50 was a placeholder to differentiate passive vs active playstyles
The Cube Mutation System (Phase 2) already handles this balance naturally — passive players earn more per cube because cubes mutate and gain value over time
The flat reduction was redundant, confusing, and even the developer couldn't tell it was working correctly without checking the math manually
Removing it makes the system transparent and honest — what the rate label shows is exactly what you earn

Passive Tick Speed Upgrade (Replaces Passive Rate Upgrade)

Instead of upgrading from 50% to 100% passive rate, the research upgrade becomes:

Passive Tick Speed — ticks happen more frequently (e.g. every 5s → every 3s → every 1s)
This is a cleaner, more understandable upgrade — faster ticks = more frequent payouts
Ties into the Passive Research Branch in Phase 4

