Balance Branch — Third Playstyle (Phase 4)

Who This Player Is

Players who are semi-AFK, doing schoolwork, or running a light autoclicker. They click more than pure passive but never build up to max hold multiplier. Currently they get a watered-down version of both Active and Passive with no dedicated advantage.

Design Problem

Without dedicated mechanics, Balance players are just worse at everything — they never hit 5x multiplier, and they never let cubes sit long enough for full passive benefit. They need their own advantage that rewards consistent moderate engagement rather than peak engagement or pure patience.

Candidate Mechanics (to decide in Phase 4)

Streak System — consecutive hatchery cycles without going fully idle give a stacking streak bonus
Hybrid Rate Formula — research that scales off BOTH active rate and passive count: bonus = sqrt(activeRate * passiveRate) — peaks when both are moderate
Tempo Bonus — combo meter that builds when producing within a target rate window (not too fast, not too slow)
Autoclicker Legitimization — official auto-click research upgrade that keeps player permanently in 1.5x-2x multiplier range, acknowledging the semi-AFK demographic fairly

Key Design Principle

Should NOT require being at the device constantly (that's Active)
Should require MORE engagement than pure AFK (that's Passive)
Rewards checking in every few minutes rather than every few seconds or never
Autoclicker players are a valid demographic — lean into it rather than fight it

Added end of Phase 1 — to be designed and implemented in Phase 4

